      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "No, aspirin should never be given to children. It can cause Reye's syndrome, a rare but serious condition. Instead, give your child plenty of fluids, keep them comfortable, and consult a doctor for appropriate fever-reducing medications, such as acetaminophen or ibuprofen. It's important to use age-appropriate dosages.",
